The paper focuses on the joint estimation of a 3D map from lidar data and images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image processing and robotics (RO) for autonomous driving. The paper also mentions the use of surface reconstruction algorithms in computer graphics (GR), which suggests a possible connection to computer graphics (CG) as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a framework that combines accuracy and dense information, which could involve machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.GR, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
